<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910703-0028</DOCNO><DOCID>910703-0028.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Tie/communications Inc.:   Sale of Distribution Rights   To Nitsuko Is Completed</HL><DATE>07/03/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   J.NTO TIE</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY (CMT)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>CONNECTICUT (CT)FAR EAST (FE)JAPAN (JA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   TIE/communications Inc., Seymour, Conn., said it completedthe sale of rights to its equipment distribution channels toa unit of Nitsuko Ltd. of Japan.   Under the agreement, Nitsuko American gains the right todistribute both its own telephone equipment and productsdesigned by TIE through supply companies, independentinterconnect companies and regional Bell operating companies.In exchange, TIE said it will receive $9 million forinventories and royalties on sales to its former customersfor several years. Nitsuko will also provide technical andcustomer support to former TIE customers.</LP><TEXT>   TIE, which just emerged from Chapter 11 bankruptcy-lawproceedings, said it will continue to distribute products itdesigned, as well as Nitsuko equipment, through its owndirect sales and service network. Nitsuko American willcontinue to manufacture equipment for TIE and will provideongoing research and development.</TEXT></DOC>